  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nMy beacon client was running for about 1 week uninterrupted and suddenly began to fail.\r\n\r\n`Dec 28 17:01:05.696 CRIT Failed to start beacon node reason: Failed to build beacon chain: Unable to get fork choice head: ProtoArrayError(\"find_head failed: InvalidBestNode { start_root: 0xa498fe73df9ac05d997b9ca092b294eae91eb8e239946133e177ba3f684be028, justified_epoch: Epoch(6050), finalized_epoch: Epoch(6048), head_root: 0xa498fe73df9ac05d997b9ca092b294eae91eb8e239946133e177ba3f684be028, head_justified_epoch: Epoch(6048), head_finalized_epoch: Epoch(6047) }\")`\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nDocker `sigp/lighthouse:v1.0.4`\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nFixed by deleting beacon folder and restarting client. I didn't have the foresight to retain the logs or data from the beacon folder, but I still have metrics for this time period if those would be helpful.\r\n",
